&nbsp;

The cash flow in Year 3 when converted into dollars is **$ 3,762,230**.

First, we will get the present value of Year 1:

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Present Value } &= \dfrac{\text{Cash Flow in \$ }}{\text{(1 + Discount Rate)}^t}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{\$ 3,614,123 }}{\text{1 +.12 }^1}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{\$ 3,614,123 }}{\text{1.12 }^1}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{\$ 3,614,123 }}{\text{1.12 }}\\[15pt]
&=\boxed{\text{\$ 3,226,896}}
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;

The present value in Year 1 is **$ 3,226,896**.

Next, we will get the present value of Year 2:

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Present Value } &= \dfrac{\text{Cash Flow in \$ }}{\text{(1 + Discount Rate)}^t}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{\$ 3,650,660 }}{\text{1 +.12 }^2}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{\$ 3,650,660 }}{\text{1.12 }^2}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{\$ 3,650,660}}{\text{1.2544 }}\\[15pt]
&=\boxed{\text{\$ 2,910,284}}
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;

The present value in Year 2 is **$ 2,910,284**.

Next, we will get the present value of Year 3:

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Present Value } &= \dfrac{\text{Cash Flow in \$ }}{\text{(1 + Discount Rate)}^t}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{\$ 3,687,595 }}{\text{1 +.12 }^3}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{\$ 3,687,595 }}{\text{1.12 }^3}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{\$ 3,687,595}}{\text{1.4049 }}\\[15pt]
