&nbsp;

The present value in Year 5 is **$ 2,134,841**.

Applying the formula:

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{$R_{Fc}$} &=\text{$R_{US}$}-\text{$h_{US}$}+\text{$h_{FC}$}\\
&=\text{0.12}-\text{0.05}+\text{0.04}\\

&=\boxed{\text{11 \%}}
\end{aligned}$$

&nbsp;

The required return in Swiss franc is **11%**

Next, we will determine the NPV in Swiss franc. We need to determine the present value of the cash inflow after 5 years. First, we will compute the present value in Year 1.
$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Present Value } &= \dfrac{\text{Cash Flow in SF }}{\text{(1+Required Return)}^t}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{SF 3,900,000 }}{\text{1.11}^1}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{SF 3,900,000 }}{\text{1.11 }^1}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{SF 3,900,000 }}{\text{1.11 }}\\[15pt]
&=\boxed{\text{SF 3,513,514}}
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;

The present value in Year 1 is **SF 3,513,514**.

Next, we will compute the present value in Year 2.
$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Present Value } &= \dfrac{\text{Cash Flow in SF }}{\text{(1+Required Return)}^t}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{SF 3,900,000 }}{\text{1.11}^2}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{SF 3,900,000 }}{\text{1.11 }^2}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{SF 3,900,000 }}{\text{1.2321 }}\\[15pt]
&=\boxed{\text{SF 3,165,327}}
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;

The present value in Year 2 is **SF 3,165,327**.

Next, we will compute the present value in Year 3.
$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Present Value } &= \dfrac{\text{Cash Flow in SF }}{\text{(1+Required Return)}^t}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{SF 3,900,000 }}{\text{1.11}^3}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{SF 3,900,000 }}{\text{1.11 }^3}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{SF 3,900,000 }}{\text{1.3676 }}\\[15pt]
&=\boxed{\text{SF 2,851,646}}
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;

The present value in Year 3 is **SF 2,851,646**.

Next, we will compute the present value in Year 4.
$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Present Value } &= \dfrac{\text{Cash Flow in SF }}{\text{(1+Required Return)}^t}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{SF 3,900,000 }}{\text{1.11}^4}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{SF 3,900,000 }}{\text{1.11 }^4}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{SF 3,900,000 }}{\text{1.5181 }}\\[15pt]
&=\boxed{\text{SF 2,569,051}}
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;

The present value in Year 4 is **SF  2,569,051**.

Lastly, we will compute the present value in Year 5.
$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Present Value } &= \dfrac{\text{Cash Flow in \$ }}{\text{(1+Required Return)}^t}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{SF 3,900,000 }}{\text{1.11}^5}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{SF 3,900,000 }}{\text{1.11 }^5}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{SF 3,900,000 }}{\text{1.5181 }}\\[15pt]
&=\boxed{\text{SF 2,314,460}}
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;

The present value in Year 5 is **SF  2,314,460**.

Now that we have determined the NPV in Swiss franc, we will now convert it into U.S. dollars.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{NPV in \$} &= \dfrac{\text{NPV in SF }}{\text{Spot Rate}}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{SF 613,998 }}{\text{SF 1.09}}\\[15pt]
&=\boxed{\text{\$ 563,301}}
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;

The NPV in dollars is **$ 563,301**.
